Bekaert Plans to Boost Production in Slovakia, Hospodarske Says

-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 
2011-07-20T06:43:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/bekaert-plans-to-boost-production-in-slovakia-hospodarske-says.html
Bekaert SA (BEKB)  plans to invest up to 40
million euros ($57 million) to expand production in Slovakia,
Hospodarske Noviny  reported .  The Belgian maker of steel cords used in tires will create
about 400 new jobs at its factory in Sladkovicovo, southern
Slovakia, the newspaper said, citing city Mayor Anton Szabo.  Bekaert already employs more than 2,200 people in its two
factories in Slovakia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
 rtomek@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net . 